# Lab 006 - Wazuh SIEM Installation, Validation, and Dashboard Access Troubleshooting

## Executive Summary

This lab documents the installation and validation of a dedicated Wazuh SIEM server in a local UTM lab environment. The Wazuh server was installed on Ubuntu Server 24.04.4 ARM64 with sufficient CPU, memory, and storage resources. After installation, the Wazuh manager, indexer, and dashboard services were validated, listening ports were checked, and dashboard access was confirmed through the browser.

This lab was not only a basic installation exercise. It also included deployment validation, LVM storage expansion, installer troubleshooting, service verification, port validation, dashboard access troubleshooting, and secure credential handling.

## Objective

The objective of this lab was to deploy a dedicated Wazuh all-in-one SIEM server and validate that the core Wazuh components were running correctly before moving into agent deployment and alert triage.

