## LVM Expansion

During post-installation validation, the virtual disk was 55 GB, but the root filesystem initially used only about 26 GB. The unused LVM free space was identified and allocated to the root logical volume before installing Wazuh.

Commands used:

lsblk  
sudo vgs  
sudo lvs  
sudo lvextend -l +100%FREE /dev/ubuntu-vg/ubuntu-lv  
sudo resize2fs /dev/ubuntu-vg/ubuntu-lv  
df -h  

Observed state before expansion:

Physical disk: 55G  
Volume group: 51.95G  
Root logical volume: 25.97G  
Free LVM space: 25.97G  

Observed state after expansion:

Root filesystem: 51G  
Available space: 42G  
Logical volume: <51.95G  

This ensured that the Wazuh server had enough usable disk space before SIEM installation.

