## Installer Validation

The first generic Wazuh installer URL returned an XML AccessDenied response instead of a Bash script.

Observed invalid installer output:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>  
<Error><Code>AccessDenied</Code><Message>Access Denied</Message></Error>  

The invalid file was removed, and a version-specific Wazuh installer path was used instead.

Commands used:

rm wazuh-install.sh  
curl -L -O https://packages.wazuh.com/4.14/wazuh-install.sh  
head -5 wazuh-install.sh  
file wazuh-install.sh  
ls -lh wazuh-install.sh  

Validated installer output:

#!/bin/bash  

# Wazuh installer  
# Copyright (C) 2015, Wazuh Inc.  

wazuh-install.sh: Bourne-Again shell script, ASCII text executable  

The installer file was confirmed to be a valid Bash script before execution.

## Wazuh Installation

The Wazuh all-in-one installation was started with:

sudo bash ./wazuh-install.sh -a

The installation generated administrator credentials. These credentials were stored locally and were not uploaded to GitHub.

