## Port Validation

Listening ports were checked with:

sudo ss -tulpen | grep -E "443|5601|9200|1514|1515|55000"

Observed result:

443   → Wazuh dashboard  
1514  → Agent communication  
1515  → Agent enrollment  
55000 → Wazuh API  
9200  → Wazuh indexer on localhost  

The Wazuh dashboard service was active and listening on HTTPS port 443.

## Dashboard Access Troubleshooting

The dashboard initially did not open in the browser. Service and port validation confirmed that Wazuh was running correctly, so browser access and IP usage were checked.

The incorrect IP address was entered first:

https://192.168.4.9

The correct IP address was identified from the VM network interface:

192.168.64.9

Correct dashboard URL:

https://192.168.64.9

After using the correct IP address, the Wazuh dashboard was successfully accessed through the browser.

