## Analysis

The Wazuh installation was successful. The core services were running, port 443 was listening, and the dashboard was accessible from the browser. The absence of registered agents is expected because no endpoint agent has been deployed yet.

The main troubleshooting steps involved validating system resources, expanding LVM storage, confirming installer integrity, checking service status, validating listening ports, and correcting the browser IP address.

The next logical step is to install a Wazuh agent on a separate Linux endpoint and begin collecting SSH authentication logs.

## Risk

No security incident was investigated in this lab.

The main operational risks identified during setup were:

- Insufficient disk allocation before LVM expansion
- Invalid installer download from a generic URL
- Browser access failure caused by incorrect IP entry
- Credential exposure risk if passwords are uploaded publicly

These risks were handled before moving into alert triage.

