## Final SOC Summary

Wazuh was successfully installed and validated as a dedicated all-in-one SIEM server in a local UTM lab environment. The Wazuh manager, indexer, and dashboard services were confirmed as active and running. Port validation confirmed that the dashboard was listening on HTTPS port 443, and browser access was successfully established using the correct server IP address. No endpoint agents were registered at this stage, so the next step is agent deployment and authentication log collection.

## Lessons Learned

- Validate VM resources before installing SIEM tools.
- Check disk allocation carefully when using LVM.
- Confirm installer integrity before execution.
- Do not force outdated installers on unsupported systems.
- Validate services, ports, IP configuration, and browser access separately.
- Store credentials locally and never upload them to GitHub.
- A realistic SOC lab should separate the SIEM server and monitored endpoint.

